    "naturalLanguage": "CDC paper / Nash-Williams tree-packing campaign step NW-3 -- the exchange lemma (Diestel's Lemma 2.4.3 / 3.5.3, the heart of the tree-packing theorem; replaces the role of cdc-lean's Kaiser machinery in NashWilliams.lean 337-3459, which cannot cross our plain-statement chaining boundary because its intermediate lemmas mention recursively-defined partition sequences): if F : Fin 3 -> Finset E is a maximum tuple of pairwise-disjoint forests (maximality quantified over all disjoint forest tuples by total cardinality) and edge e lies in no F i, then there is a vertex predicate P containing both ends of e such that any two P-vertices are connected within P by every F i. Proof machinery, all inside one declaration: exchange steps on tuples (ExStep: insert a free edge f into coordinate i and delete an edge g that bridges f's ends, encoded by non-connectivity of the ends in (G i).erase g); Reach = ReflTransGen ExStep from F; P = UU = the free-edge adjacency component of e's first end over all reachable tuples. Local have-lemmas: walk_symm (symmetric step relations reverse), subst_lemma (walks through insert f W decompose at f), exchange_forest (the exchange preserves forestness -- a second walk for a remaining edge's ends reroutes through the deleted bridge, contradiction), insert_forest (adding an edge with disconnected ends keeps a forest), hinv (Reach preserves disjointness, forestness, and per-coordinate cardinality), hfe (maximality makes every free edge's ends connected in every coordinate -- else inserting it grows the tuple), hA (Diestel's key claim: a free edge's ends with one end in UU are connected within UU in every coordinate -- strong induction over connecting edge subsets: either some edge is droppable, or every edge of a minimal connecting set is a bridge in the full forest hence exchangeable, making its ends adjacent in UU and the whole walk UU-internal), htrans (walks within UU in any reachable tuple translate to F, by Reach induction, replacing inserted free edges via hA), and the final assembly chaining u back to e's end and forward to v through the adjacency component. Pre-flighted clean on the pinned lean-checker as a single 513-line declaration under set_option maxHeartbeats 200000 (the exact server budget), built incrementally over ~10 local iterations.",
